intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of this course students will be able to:
Demonstrate familiarity with the relevant modern programming environments; 
Use the command line and a text editor competently, ideally with experience with a modern IDE; 
Develop well-structured programs in Java and Python, and be proficient in looking for online help, and be prepared to pick up new skills independently;
Explain the importance of concise and informative documentation, and use modern documentation tools;
Provide evidence of program correctness through thorough testing;
Describe and use version control processes, and be able to checkout and use a repository (e.g. git);
Launch, edit and use Jupyter/Colab notebooks (including ability to work with basic operations on numpy arrays);
Use basic SQL from Java and Python, and be able to set up a basic server;
Be able to spin up a Container (e.g. Docker VM (and/or Kubernetes));
Creating/adapting a basic graphical user interface (give them some exposure to a modern GUI and how to adapt it);
Describe the basics of user interaction with the Linux shell, file navigation, system monitoring, printing;
Explain how to install and configure software under Linux, and be able to write and execute simple Linux shell scripts.
